# Force LF on checkout for all text files, on every platform. The test
# suite compares golden `.xml`/`.tex` fixtures line-by-line against
# LF-serialized output (latexml_oxide/src/util/test.rs::process_xmlfile
# splits raw bytes on '\n'), so a default Windows git (core.autocrlf=true)
# checking out CRLF would fail every regression test with stray `\r`.
# Shell scripts and the dump fixtures are equally LF-dependent.
* text=auto eol=lf
# Binary test fixtures — never subject to EOL conversion.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.pdf binary
# EPS/PS test fixtures may embed binary previews; byte-exact fixtures matter
# more than EOL uniformity here.
*.eps binary
*.ps binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.eot binary
*.ico binary

# Kernel dumps are generated by `tools/make_formats.sh` and check in at
# ~7 MB / ~110k lines each. Mark them as generated so:
#   - GitHub language stats don't count them toward repo composition
#   - `git diff` skips the inline diff (the byte-level info is rarely useful)
#   - `git log --follow` doesn't try to track per-line history
resources/dumps/*.dump.txt -diff -merge linguist-generated
resources/dumps/texlive.*.version       linguist-generated
